<subSubSection pageNumber="612" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="612">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="612">Note:</emphasis>
Stearn (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="612">J. Arnold Arbor.</emphasis>
52: 630. 1971) argued that the Sloane plate must be taken as the 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
but the Plukenet plate, previously designated as type by Johnston, is original material and this earlier choice therefore has priority. Taroda &amp; Gibbs (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="612">Notes Roy. Bot. Gard. Edinburgh</emphasis>
44: 134. 1986) provide an extensive discussion.
</paragraph>
